Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveOluwasegun Bolarinwa, a fake Army General has been arrested for alleged N270million fraud.
Bolarinwa was picked up by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) at Alagbado area of Lagos on Wednesday, January 12, 2022..

Before his arrested, the suspect claimed President Muhammadu Buhari had shortlisted him and one other at large as the next Chief of Army Staff (COAS).


EFCC spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren, noted that BolarinwaÂ forged a letter of appointment as COAS purportedly signed by Buhari and showed the same to the victim.
Items such as pump action guns, three cartridge bullets, a swagger stick and several forged documents were recovered from him.

